The verse does not speak to the issue, as there is no definition of what is Scripture and what is not.  Only Tradition has told us what is Scripture.  As Orthodox Scripture is part of Tradition, and the foundation, but it does not stand outside of that Tradition.<br>
Jeff the Finn <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://s88610834.onlinehome.us/Orthodox/index.html" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://s88610834.onlinehome.us/skunks.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=peaches116>peaches116</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style=color:green;><b>Dream Writer<br>40 pts.</b></span></span><br>  Posts: 644<br> <font color=#B87333>(11/10/03 9:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=45>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.onerefuge.com/stitch.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Just a reminder....</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Then some Pharisees and teachers of the law came to Jesus from Jerusalem and asked, &quot;Why do your disciples break the tradition of the elders?  They don't wash their hands before they eat!&quot;<br>
Jesus replied, <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">&quot;And why do you break the command of God for the sake of your tradition?&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Matt. 15:1-3<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">&quot;You have let go of the commands of God and are holding on to the traditions of men.&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Mark 7:8<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>See to it that no one takes you captive through hollow and deceptive philosophy, which depends on human tradition and the basic principles of this world rather than on Christ.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Col. 2:8<br>
<br>
I can't find the word tradition used anywhere in scripture in a positive light.  Rather, every time it's brought up, it's put into a negative concept.  Even Paul talked about how he had been raised in Judaism and was extremely zealous for his father's traditions in Galatians 1:8.<br>
<br>
Jesus made a distinct difference between traditions which are from man and commands which are from God.  I see nothing in scripture to support holding to any kind of tradition, rather, I see warnings against it.  And my guess would be because God doesn't want us putting too much faith and trust in traditions.  It is possible to be so caught up in tradition that you lose sight of the truth.  Which I only say becaue I grew up in a church full of traditions. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">**********************************************<br>
