me from the canon used for the KJV, NIV, NASB, etc.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ironically, I rarely use any of those three translations, unless I don't have access to my Bibles and I'm using Blue Letter Bible online.<br>
<br>
The three I use the most are the NLT - but just for reading, it really isn't suited for study.  The NJB (New Jerusalem), kind of a Catholic NIV - modern translation, but a Catholic Bible.  Finally, I mainly use the NRSV Study Bible which includes all the books of both Catholic and Orthodox canons.<br>
<br>
And yes, no Rancor allowed here.  Very nasty to have around.<br>
